abstract: Presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's decision to back a tax on trades marks a blow for Wall Street lobbyists which had seen the moderate Democrat as a potential ally, said analysts and lobbyists.
snippet: Presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's decision to back a tax on trades marks a blow for Wall Street lobbyists which had seen the moderate Democrat as a potential ally, said analysts and lobbyists.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” Presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's decision to back a tax on trades marks a blow for Wall Street lobbyists which had seen the moderate Democrat as a potential ally, said analysts and lobbyists.
headline_main: Bloomberg's Transaction Tax Sets Stage for Clash With Wall Street Clients
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg's Transaction Tax Sets Stage for Clash With Wall Street Clients

abstract: The 2020 Democrats traded the snow drifts of Iowa and New Hampshire for the palm trees of Nevada as the campaign moved southwest last weekend. See the Nevada campaign in photos.

abstract: Michael Bloomberg faced a barrage of attacks at his first Democratic presidential debate on Wednesday, as his rivals rushed to criticize the billionaire businessman for his wealth, record on race and history of sexist comments.
